  "text": "In normal cellular processes, cells are capable of neutralizing the deleterious effects of ROS and free radicals by several intracellular and extracellular antioxidative systems. Any change in one of these systems, breaks this equilibrium leading to OS, resulting in an overall increase in cellular levels of ROS that can initiate lipid peroxidation and induce oxidative DNA damage [CITATION_1] .",
